library(tidyverse)
library(rnaturalearthdata)
library(leaflet)
library(sf)
library(tidygeocoder)
library(readxl)
library(mapview)
library(stringr)
library(leaflet.extras)

Load and wrangle data

#suzukii occurences from  rsted, I.V. and rsted, M. (2018)  doi:10.1111/1365-2664.13285. 
geocoded_suz_loc_ex <- read_excel("./JPE-Oersted-ST1.xlsx") 

#country to continent csv file taken from : https://github.com/lukes/ISO-3166-Countries-with-Regional-Codes/blob/master/all/all.csv
world_continent <- read.csv("./countries_subcontinents.csv", stringsAsFactors = F) %>%
                    janitor::clean_names() %>% 
                    dplyr::select(name, region, sub_region)

geocoded_suz_loc <- geocoded_suz_loc_ex %>% 
                            st_as_sf(coords = c("Longitude", "Latitude"), crs = 4326) %>% 
                            mutate(across('Status', str_replace, 'Few occurences', 'Few occurrences')) %>% #misspelled occurrences in the data
                            dplyr::left_join(world_continent, c("Country" = "name"))


#sf object
world_sf <- countries110 %>% 
  st_as_sf() %>% filter(name != "Antarctica" )

Fill by year D. suzukii was recorded

geocoded_suz_loc$Year[geocoded_suz_loc$sub_region == "South-eastern Asia" ] <- "Native"

label_year_occurrence_pop <- function(Year, Status) {
  
  paste("<b>Year found:</b>", Year, #function to add label and status 
        "<br>",
        "<b>Occurence:</b>", Status) 
}

pal_year <- colorFactor(c("#F7FBFF", "#DEEBF7", "#C6DBEF", "#9ECAE1", "#6BAED6", "#4292C6", "#2171B5","#08519C", "#08306B", "#000066", "000033", "pink"), c("1980", "2008", "2009", "2010", "2011", "2012", "2013", "2014", "2015", "2016", "2017", "Native" ))

leaflet() %>% 
  addPolygons(data = world_sf,
              fillColor = "darkolivegreen",
              fillOpacity = 1,
              color = "black",
              label = ~name,
              weight = 1
              ) %>% 
  addCircleMarkers(data = geocoded_suz_loc,
                   weight = .5,
                   fillColor = ~pal_year(Year),
                   color = "black",
                   fillOpacity = 1,   
                  popup = ~label_year_occurrence_pop(Year, Status),
                   radius= 3.3) %>% 
              addLegend(data = geocoded_suz_loc,
                        pal = pal_year,
                        values = ~Year,
                        opacity = 1,
                        title = 'Year documented') %>%
          setMapWidgetStyle(style = list(background = "white"))

Zoom in on Europe

geo_europe <- geocoded_suz_loc[geocoded_suz_loc$region == "Europe",] 

pal_year <- colorFactor(c("#F7FBFF", "#DEEBF7", "#C6DBEF", "#9ECAE1", "#6BAED6", "#4292C6", "#2171B5","#08519C", "#08306B", "#000066", "000033", "pink"), c("1980", "2008", "2009", "2010", "2011", "2012", "2013", "2014", "2015", "2016", "2017", "Native" ))

world_sf_europe <- world_sf %>% 
  filter(continent == "Europe") %>%
  filter(name != "Russia") 
  


leaflet() %>% 
  addPolygons(data = world_sf_europe,
              fillColor = "darkolivegreen",
              fillOpacity = 1,
              color = "black",
              label = ~name,
              weight = 1
              ) %>% 
  addCircleMarkers(data = geo_europe,
                   weight = .5,
                   fillColor = ~pal_year(Year),
                   color = "black",
                   fillOpacity = 1,  
                   radius= 3.3,
                   popup = ~label_year_occurrence_pop(Year, Status)) %>%  
  addLegend(data = geo_europe,
                   pal = pal_year,
                   values = ~Year,
                   opacity = 1,
                   title = 'Year documented') %>%
  setMapWidgetStyle(style = list(background = "white"))
